<title>NETHERLANDS: Reed-Elsevier buying MDL Information Systems.</title>
<headline>Reed-Elsevier buying MDL Information Systems.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM, Netherlands</dateline>
<text>
<p>Anglo-Dutch publishing group Reed-Elsevier said Monday it agreed to buy MDL Information Systems Inc. of California for $320 million.</p>
<p>Reed-Elsevier said its Elsevier Science unit would offer about $32 a share for all outstanding shares in MDL, which provides data bases and support services, primarily to the life sciences and chemical industries.</p>
<p>MDL, which is based in San Leandro, Calif., posted net profits of $11 million on revenues of $62 million in the year ended March 31, 1996.</p>
<p>Reed-Elsevier said it would use part of its short-term dollar deposit accounts in the United States to finance the purchase.</p>
